  "summaries": [
    {"book":"Leviticus","chapter":1,"summary":"The Lord instructs Moses on the proper procedure for burnt offerings of cattle, sheep, goats, and birds as a sweet savour."},
    {"book":"Leviticus","chapter":2,"summary":"Laws for the meat (grain) offering of fine flour with oil and frankincense, including baked, pan, and firstfruits variations."},
    {"book":"Leviticus","chapter":3,"summary":"Regulations for peace offerings from the herd and the flock, with instructions on the fat and blood prohibitions."},
    {"book":"Leviticus","chapter":4,"summary":"The sin offering is established for unintentional sins by the priest, the whole congregation, a ruler, and a common person."},
    {"book":"Leviticus","chapter":5,"summary":"Trespass offerings for various offenses including touching unclean things, rash oaths, and sins requiring restitution."},
    {"book":"Leviticus","chapter":6,"summary":"Further laws on trespass offerings with restitution, and priestly instructions for the burnt offering, meat offering, and sin offering."},
    {"book":"Leviticus","chapter":7,"summary":"Laws for the trespass offering and peace offering, including the wave breast and heave shoulder for priests, and prohibitions on fat and blood."},
    {"book":"Leviticus","chapter":8,"summary":"Moses consecrates Aaron and his sons as priests, washing, clothing, and anointing them, and offering sacrifices for their ordination."},
    {"book":"Leviticus","chapter":9,"summary":"Aaron offers his first sacrifices as high priest; the glory of the Lord appears, and fire from the Lord consumes the offering."},
    {"book":"Leviticus","chapter":10,"summary":"Nadab and Abihu offer strange fire before the Lord and are killed; Moses instructs the remaining priests on proper conduct and mourning."},
    {"book":"Leviticus","chapter":11,"summary":"Dietary laws distinguishing clean and unclean animals, fish, birds, and creeping things, with the charge to be holy as God is holy."},
    {"book":"Leviticus","chapter":12,"summary":"Laws of purification for a woman after childbirth, with prescribed offerings for her cleansing."},
    {"book":"Leviticus","chapter":13,"summary":"Detailed instructions for the priest to diagnose and manage leprosy and other skin diseases, including quarantine procedures."},
    {"book":"Leviticus","chapter":14,"summary":"The ritual for cleansing a healed leper involving two birds, cedar wood, scarlet, and hyssop, plus offerings for atonement and restoration."},
    {"book":"Leviticus","chapter":15,"summary":"Laws regarding ceremonial uncleanness from bodily discharges for both men and women, with prescribed purification rituals."},
    {"book":"Leviticus","chapter":16,"summary":"The Day of Atonement (Yom Kippur): Aaron enters the Holy of Holies with blood, the scapegoat bears Israel's sins into the wilderness."},
    {"book":"Leviticus","chapter":17,"summary":"All sacrifices must be brought to the tabernacle; the life of the flesh is in the blood, and eating blood is strictly prohibited."},
    {"book":"Leviticus","chapter":18,"summary":"Prohibitions against sexual immorality, incest, and the abominations of the Canaanites, with warnings of the land vomiting out its inhabitants."},
    {"book":"Leviticus","chapter":19,"summary":"The holiness code: love thy neighbour as thyself, honor parents, keep the sabbath, leave gleanings for the poor, and practice just weights."},
    {"book":"Leviticus","chapter":20,"summary":"Penalties for Molech worship, consulting familiar spirits, cursing parents, and various sexual sins; a call to separate and be holy."},
    {"book":"Leviticus","chapter":21,"summary":"Holiness requirements for priests regarding mourning, marriage, and physical qualifications for those who offer the bread of God."},
    {"book":"Leviticus","chapter":22,"summary":"Rules for priestly cleanness when handling holy things, and requirements that all offerings to the Lord must be without blemish."},
    {"book":"Leviticus","chapter":23,"summary":"The feasts of the Lord: Sabbath, Passover, Unleavened Bread, Firstfruits, Pentecost, Trumpets, Day of Atonement, and Tabernacles."},
    {"book":"Leviticus","chapter":24,"summary":"Instructions for the lamp and showbread; an Israelite blasphemes and is stoned; the law of an eye for an eye is established."},
    {"book":"Leviticus","chapter":25,"summary":"The sabbatical year (every 7th) and the Jubilee (every 50th): land rest, liberty for servants, and economic restoration through redemption."},
    {"book":"Leviticus","chapter":26,"summary":"Blessings promised for obedience (rain, peace, plenty) and curses for disobedience (disease, famine, exile), with a promise to remember the covenant."},
    {"book":"Leviticus","chapter":27,"summary":"Laws for the valuation and redemption of persons, animals, houses, and fields dedicated to the Lord by vow."}
  ],
